Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.46,0:01:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, the oneness of the evolution then, up through the animal kingdom, up through\Nthe levels of the 200s, up through that which doesn't have within it enough energy, it has
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.42,0:01:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to go out and eat others because it lacks energy, not because it's wicked or because\Nit's bad, because it doesn't have within itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.88,0:01:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, as we sacrifice our personal lives for the welfare of others, as we in this room\Ndo so for the sake of the world, then by that intention do we sanctify the world, sanctify
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.93,0:01:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,human life.\NIt's by our intention that human life becomes sanctified, all that's personified in the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.21,0:01:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,life of Jesus Christ.\NThe message radiates out 2,000 years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.22,0:01:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So as we support that energy now, then we are serving life right this moment, right\Nthis moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.48,0:02:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We are, all of us, collectively serving the welfare of all of human life.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.54,0:02:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us see if that's a fact.\NThat's a fact, O Lord Jesus, that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.70,0:02:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to ask, what can I do, do me a favor, don't do anything.\NStop doing things, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.48,0:02:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be the fulfillment of the potentiality.\NThis is the fulfillment of the potentiality which you have karmically inherited, or you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.52,0:02:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,would never be in a room like this, because a room like this is full of people destined\Nfor enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.76,0:02:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone that is in this room is destined for enlightenment.\NThat's a fact, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.66,0:02:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NIt is a fact, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.66,0:03:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, why else would you be here?\NWhy else would you be here, if this was...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.17,0:03:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.\NHey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.23,0:03:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,People destined to become tennis players are at a class on tennis this afternoon.\NPeople destined to become enlightened are in a class on being enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.96,0:03:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What else would you expect?\NEveryone here then has to own that within themself that you all innately have elected
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.53,0:03:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,by your own free will to be that which upholds all of life in its expression in its humanity\Nby your very being here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.33,0:03:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This very moment we are upholding.\NWe are a part of that 15% that's upholding the other 85% just by the virtue of our commitment
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.61,0:03:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to truth, to learn about truth, to my sharing with you what I've learned about truth and\Nwhat I hope will be useful to the world and in today's world, its application to world
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.61,0:04:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,peace and bringing about peace.\NHow to express that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.18,0:04:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That intelligence, how to express that intelligence in our international diplomacy.\NSo spirituality is just not a Sunday morning thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.66,0:04:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being in the world.\NIt's a way of being in the world that by its sheer intention tends to bring forth truth
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.44,0:04:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and integrity in others because non-integrity when it's confronted by integrity tends to\Ncringe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.86,0:04:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It pulls back from the light.\NSo just being what you are tends to suppress non-integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.28,0:04:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Being what you are radiates out an energy field and light.\NThe collective consciousness of mankind keeps evolving and it's going to continue further.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.58,0:04:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw on that curve how it's going like this and how it's going like that.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.82,0:04:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level of mankind is rapidly moving.\NSo this group here is in the forefront of that graph.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.54,0:05:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We're right there where it's at.\NThis is about as far as consciousness has evolved up to this point which you're hearing today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.22,0:05:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly.\NConsciousness has evolved any further than this point in a way that can be communicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.14,0:05:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NIn a way that can be communicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.54,0:05:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Certain information is transformational.\NIt has within itself a transformational power.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.74,0:05:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So we share with you information which in and of itself, in and of itself with no effort\Non your part.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.56,0:05:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Please put in no effort at all.\NNo effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.51,0:05:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To just be with the information is already transformative.\NThereby, your life becomes a prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.12,0:05:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you become a blessing to the world by the nature of your own existence.\NAnd so prayerfully, we'll stop for the day for the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.16,0:06:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to take a little longer time for questions and answers later.\NSo we'll take a break, and then we'll do questions and answers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.20,0:06:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and try to fulfill what is being unanswered in your mind.\NI'm very Christian, so I'm very Christian.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.02,0:06:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so our collective intention is impacting the world.\NI can hear it. It's ringing. It's shaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.72,0:06:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYes, we're going to do Nico's chant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.09,0:07:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we're going to have the questions and answers.\NNow we have to change microphones.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.30,0:07:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who have not been here before are not aware that Nico does the Lotus Sutra.\NChant it in Sanskrit. It's magical. Calibrates over 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.43,0:07:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Nico chanting the Lotus Sutra in Sanskrit is a rare opportunity,\Nwhich we've all earned through karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.46,0:07:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmic merit.\NKarmic merit. Take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.29,0:07:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NThe last of you want to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.99,0:12:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we're going to start the questions and answers.\NThe great people with questions on this side of the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.12,0:13:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the people with just one book signed on that side of the room.\NThis question I wrote down because I wanted to get it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.47,0:13:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.\NBecause I've been thinking about it for some time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.77,0:13:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.\NIt's a question about karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.11,0:13:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou have written that choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.83,0:13:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That choice supersedes karma, and that at a consciousness level...\NIt doesn't supersede. It determines it. Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.05,0:13:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. And that at a consciousness level of 600 or higher, you transcend personal karma.\NMy question is, is it possible, say after going through the course of miracles or something like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.84,0:13:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to choose not to be subject to karma below the level of 600?\NWhat would be choosing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.57,0:13:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego.\NThe ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.49,0:13:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the ego persists...\NYou said it, the karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.58,0:13:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 600, it's irrelevant.\NDivinity is all that exists, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.43,0:13:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.78,0:14:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NAs a contribution to the good and welfare...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.22,0:14:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.\NHe wants a hug now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.78,0:14:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,By golly.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.18,0:14:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.15,0:14:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NSo, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.27,0:14:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.73,0:14:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's funny.\NIt's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.22,0:14:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's just wonderful being here in your presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.14,0:14:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel that you've...\NThere you have to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.50,0:14:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Right in there.\NIs it this one she speaks into?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.46,0:14:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWhat is this one doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.40,0:14:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the satellite room.\NOh, the satellite room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.38,0:14:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.09,0:14:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really...\NYou're really a blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.67,0:14:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NThank you so much for your presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.63,0:14:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And this was really...\NIt was really wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.88,0:15:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you enjoyed it.\NI have a question about non-resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.45,0:15:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We've had...\NA friend of mine and I have had some really good luck
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.31,0:15:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,following your idea of if you have an acute injury\Nthat you let go of the resistance to the pain
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.54,0:15:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you say more and more.\NAnd it's been really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.68,0:15:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It works really, really well.\NAnd so what we...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.20,0:15:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm wanting to ask you is\Nhow do you take that to some chronic type of illness
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.40,0:15:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,like ringing of the ears or something like that?\NThe same thing applies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.89,0:15:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You let go resisting it\Nbecause that intensifies your focus and concentration on it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.25,0:15:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which tends to magnify the experience.\NYou become the field in which it's happening
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.26,0:16:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and let go resisting it.\NAnd what happens is it becomes forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.94,0:16:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't...\NYou can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.80,0:16:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you recall it, you'll re-experience it, say.\NBut you'll find that most things,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.10,0:16:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't pay attention to them,\Nthey're not within the focus of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.14,0:16:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And even though they're still there,\Nthey don't bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.06,0:16:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If I focus, you know, on the site of the amputation,\NI can feel the pain of it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.75,0:16:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because the pain of it never really physically disappears.\NAs far as the source of suffering, it disappears
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.32,0:16:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because...\Nyou just ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.32,0:16:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So you begin by ignoring it\Nand letting go of wanting to change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.82,0:16:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And also there's certain karmic undoingness going on with it.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.36,0:16:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I wondered if that might not be the case.\NI think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.80,0:16:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I've recalled in front of this group\Nor similar groups, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.74,0:17:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,very specific recall of exactly what the karmic indebtedness was\Nthat accounted for the excruciating experience
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.38,0:17:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that I went through at one time.\NAnd I remember extremely well what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.17,0:17:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo if that's the case, if it's a karmic undoing,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.31,0:17:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,then we should just go with that karmic undoing.\NAnd that's also a way of non-resisting it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.37,0:17:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of letting go of the resistance.\NYes, that would be a way of intellectually contextualizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.73,0:17:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Just saying.\NThat I don't know what this serves,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.45,0:17:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but for thee, O Lord, do I accept it and surrender to thy will.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.99,0:17:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAnd just go with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.05,0:17:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,For however long it goes,\Nbecause that's your karmic undoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.07,0:17:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.64,0:17:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I've also heard you say that\Nif you want to disappear something,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.68,0:17:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,accept it totally.\NSo if you go ahead and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.51,0:18:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,well, this is karmic undoing,\Nand then you focus on becoming one with the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.04,0:18:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,like you said,\Nand focus on the higher spiritual qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.84,0:18:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the first thing you do is,\Nyou stop labeling it, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.18,0:18:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,indigestion, asthma, or whatever you're calling it.\NYou don't give it any name,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.84,0:18:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're not experiencing asthma.\NYou're not experiencing arthritis.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.66,0:18:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you do is let go of calling it anything.\NThen you're only left with sensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.31,0:18:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally, if you let go of resisting a local pain,\Nstop calling it pain,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.27,0:18:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize that it's only sensation.\NThen you let go of trying,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.80,0:18:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that your mind is localizing it.\NIf you constantly let go of resisting it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.21,0:18:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the sensation will become general.\NYou can tell it's gone into your aura.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.68,0:19:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the pain or the nausea or whatever it is\Nthat you're letting go of resisting
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.14,0:19:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes general instead of specific.\NAnd you just keep surrendering to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.28,0:19:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and it becomes like diffuse in your whole aura\Nrather than localized to your ankle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.80,0:19:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You just do that as a process.\NAnd just continue to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.61,0:19:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.19,0:19:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a choice?\NWell, I suppose I could...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.10,0:19:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like being born ugly.\NI mean, what can you do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.02,0:19:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose I could resist and resist,\Nbut that wouldn't be very wise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.08,0:19:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Any other techniques you'd like to share with us?\NThat'll do for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.72,0:19:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNow, we were in Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.94,0:19:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We were on a radio program with a guy\Nwho's called sort of a local shock jock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.76,0:19:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I really enjoyed him.\NHe was really fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.16,0:19:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was a crew of three or four of us.\NIt's a very well-known program in Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.30,0:19:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the name of it.\NMan for a cow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.40,0:19:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NCow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.18,0:19:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Man cow.\NYeah, man cow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.44,0:20:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he carries on a conversation with callers in.\NVery fast mind, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.34,0:20:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a big kick out of him.\NBut one of his crew standing around,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.32,0:20:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we all have to stand up.\NYou don't get to sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.94,0:20:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You stand up.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.14,0:20:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,One of his crew,\Nuh, is just plain stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.74,0:20:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And he'll tell you,\NI'm just, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.56,0:20:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't help it.\NI just am stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.22,0:20:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he'll say something.\NAnd by God, it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.96,0:20:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it is really stupid.\NAnd it just breaks up everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.66,0:20:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this stupid guy just accepts that he's stupid.\NHe doesn't battle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.56,0:20:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know,\Nhe probably makes more than you and I
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.10,0:20:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of us put together, you know.\NJust being stupid, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.38,0:20:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He just says,\Nhe says really dumb things, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.26,0:20:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, I want a hamburger or something.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.76,0:20:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, like, in the middle of a question like that,\Nyou say, I want a hamburger, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.76,0:20:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a dumb thing to say\Nwhen a person's asking you a question, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.88,0:21:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But, uh, so totally accepting that you're stupid\Nand ugly can be very beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.16,0:21:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.52,0:21:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, what you, what you accept about yourself,\Nwhat am I supposed to do with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.64,0:21:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.\NOh, what you accept about yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.04,0:21:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody can hit you there, understand?\NSensitive people are people who have not accepted
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.62,0:21:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,their downside, and they're defensive.\NTherefore, they're vulnerable all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.58,0:21:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If you accept, if you sit down, I advise the people,\Nsit down and list every single possible defect
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.46,0:21:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have or could be perceived as having,\Nand let, and it's okay with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.82,0:21:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay with me.\NOnce it's okay with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.88,0:21:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what could be said to you that would upset you?\NYou've already accepted that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.32,0:21:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've completely disarmed the other side\Nby accepting your downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.68,0:22:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're short and skinny,\Nand you're never gonna make the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.68,0:22:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NYou're not tall enough to make the swimming team.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.82,0:22:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're too frail to be out there on the court.\NYou just ain't never gonna be an athlete.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.99,0:22:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that's a fact.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.82,0:22:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I've just never been very good at it.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.81,0:22:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Four eyes.\NOne time we were, after, after,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.47,0:22:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been four eyes too.\NAfter A Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.77,0:22:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,after A Course in Miracles meeting,\Nyou know, Lower East Side in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.11,0:22:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Famous Jewish restaurant.\NDinner goes on for about three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.82,0:22:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They stagger out of there.\NAnd on the corner is this bag lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.74,0:22:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And here are these black plastic bags\Nfull of New York City garbage sitting on the curb.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.28,0:22:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And this, right out of a movie,\Nbag lady is poking around through these things, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.71,0:22:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So we all stand around and ask for a miracle,\Nand we all bless her and send her her love.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.67,0:22:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Our love.\NAll of a sudden, her head comes out of these pile
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.73,0:23:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of black plastic bags, you know?\NAnd she looks at me and she says,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.99,0:23:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you looking at, four eyes?\NOh yeah, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.62,0:23:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you so much.\NOh, can I have a hug?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.63,0:23:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,A hug. I don't know.\NYes, maybe you can have a hug.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.49,0:23:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't knock the flowers over.\NCould I get Sharon Raine to go to the bookstore, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.99,0:23:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sharon Raine.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.78,0:23:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, okay.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.62,0:23:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What are all these here?\NThey have to sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.30,0:23:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I sign them yet?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.98,0:23:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, glad somebody keeps track of it.\NYes, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.04,0:24:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this one, all beat up.\NHoly catfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.96,0:24:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIs unconditional love a realistic intention for?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.85,0:24:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,An average American?\NCertainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.99,0:24:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Is unconditional love a realistic intention?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.60,0:24:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why wouldn't it be, huh?\NAll you have to do is let go of your reservations about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.44,0:24:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,judgmentalism and all that.\NYou see, unconditional love is a way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.14,0:24:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not something you do.\NLove is, you know, love at 500 is between a this and a that,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.20,0:24:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a me and a you, you and your cat, you and your dog, whatever.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.35,0:24:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,At 540, it becomes a way of being in the world.\NIt's just the way you are in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.45,0:24:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lovingness towards all of life and all of its expressions,\Nand a sense of humor about everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.69,0:25:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and also the capacity to see the beauty of all things.\NIt's a way of being in the world, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.03,0:25:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not something you do.\NBecause it's a way of being, therefore, it's not something that requires effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.66,0:25:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to try to be unconditionally loving.\NYou just become that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.40,0:25:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You become that.\NThe flowers are glad to see you arrive, because you're not going to pick them unnecessarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.63,0:25:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You revere all the beauty and all its innate incredible perfection.\NYou have to be careful, because you won't be able to function.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.44,0:25:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's just if you let the energy of the beauty radiate for it,\Nthen the questions and answers come to a stop,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.16,0:25:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because you become one with that field, because beauty is innate to divinity, you know, except\Nfor some people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.68,0:26:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're ugly.\NAll right, we'll move along.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.68,0:26:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NCould I possibly have a hug?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.94,0:26:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have a hug if you don't knock the flowers over.\NYes, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.01,0:26:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NDr. Hawkins, would you comment on the relationship between love and passion?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.86,0:26:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWhat's the difference between consciousness and schizophrenia?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.80,0:26:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not really related.\NThey're not really related.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.78,0:26:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is an overall nonlinear field.\NSchizophrenia is a disorganization of content, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.73,0:27:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The linear content follows certain laws, and when it gets fractured, we call it schizophrenia.\NSchizophrenia is the loss of the capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.61,0:27:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't differentiate between the categories, as described by Immanuel Kant.\NThere are various levels of abstraction, and when you confuse the material with the intellectual,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.40,0:27:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,when you lose the differentiation of levels of abstraction, then you're no longer following\Nthe order of logic, subject and predicate and verb, you know, and therefore you're not
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.66,0:27:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,constrained by...\Nby integrity, by the integrity of logic, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.56,0:27:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So you fall below 400, you're no longer logical.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.58,0:28:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NDr. Hawkins, you've commented before on the level of consciousness of humanity at
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.26,0:28:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the time of birth of Christ.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.26,0:28:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And also the Buddha.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.26,0:28:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How about Krishna and the Bhagavad Gita, that whole Indian history?\NCould you comment on that particular period?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.32,0:28:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWell, the Bhagavad Gita calibrates 900 or over.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.56,0:28:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The great Aryan sages, you see, 7 to 10,000 B.C., the pre-Indian culture, the Aryan, already\Nbirthed great spiritual genius, 900, 950 was the great sages, and out of the great sages
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.62,0:28:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,arose the Gitas.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.84,0:28:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And the ancient Hindu teachings.\NSo it was already old, already old.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.72,0:29:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual enlightenment was already known, you know, prior to the birth of Buddha or\NChrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.53,0:29:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't reach this side of the world because there was no communication with this side\Nof the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.63,0:29:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It was completely isolated from this side of the world.\NSo it was like reborn in the form of Jesus Christ, reborn in Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.78,0:29:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The time of the birth of Buddha, the consciousness level of mankind was...\NIt was at 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.38,0:29:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of the birth of Jesus Christ, it was at 100.\NAnd how about like at the time of Krishna?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.30,0:29:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't done all that.\NAnyway, it evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.47,0:29:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the great Aryan sages of 7 to 10,000 B.C. had already experienced the enlightened condition.\NAnd their writings are still way up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.36,0:29:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.36,0:30:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Krishna is coming back.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.36,0:30:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's correct.\NI mean, when I read what Krishna said in the Bhagavad Gita, that's exactly the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.09,0:30:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who worship me by whatever name are dear to me, and I will take them unto myself.\NThat's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.17,0:30:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.80,0:30:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question about art.\NIf...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.42,0:30:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what Michelangelo calibrated at, but would his art that came through him\Nbe able to calibrate higher than...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.42,0:30:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.25,0:31:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, the production is that of the radiance of the author.\NWriters, the writings of spiritual teachers usually calibrate about just exactly what
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.05,0:31:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the teacher's at.\NSo you're telling me what you calibrate at then, without saying it, by what your books
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.59,0:31:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate at.\NAbout Michelangelo, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.59,0:31:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I...\NYou know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.59,0:31:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just...\NI wasn't even...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.59,0:31:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I was asking...\NI'm an artist, and that's why I was asking that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.59,0:31:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But then it just clicked like, whoa.\NYeah, Michelangelo.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.59,0:31:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks...\NIt calibrated really high.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.59,0:31:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NWe calibrated Michelangelo.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.59,0:31:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, he's way up there.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.59,0:31:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.59,0:31:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I miss you, Midna.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.59,0:31:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, they personalize, they personalize it.\NIt's impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.17,0:31:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence.\NThe presence, then, you learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.23,0:31:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I...\NI...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.23,0:31:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.23,0:31:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence then utilizes the machinery, which is this body and this languaging and\Nall.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.35,0:32:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence utilizes the machinery to express itself in a form comprehensible to the audience.\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.38,0:32:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impersonal.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.64,0:32:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You were talking today about non-doing and non-effort, which is exactly opposite\Nhow I'm living my life, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.64,0:32:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-what?\NNon-doing and non-effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.64,0:32:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-doing and non-effort.\NOh, yes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.64,0:32:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an interstate.\NYou can be busy as all get out on the outer.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.64,0:32:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know, I know.\NBusy as can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.64,0:32:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it actually brings me to confronting a paradigm that I struggle with, which is,\Nis it possible for mankind to live on this planet without having to work, having to do
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.74,0:32:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the paradigm that we see out there?\NBecause it's certainly been my fantasy to live on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.74,0:32:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To be able to just be, and not have to...\NWhen you're a spirit, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.74,0:32:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I thought, well, maybe it's a certain consciousness level.\NIf you get to be a certain consciousness level, then can you truly just trust that the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.74,0:32:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,will provide everything for you, including the money, including the house, where you\Ndon't have to work a job?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.83,0:32:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.83,0:32:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.83,0:33:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.83,0:33:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.83,0:33:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.83,0:33:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.83,0:33:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.83,0:33:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.83,0:33:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.83,0:33:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.83,0:33:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NShe needs to find a job in a spiritual community or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.02,0:33:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stop resisting hunger, you don't have to work.\NWhen your material motivation disappears, there has to be some other motivation, or
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.80,0:33:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you come to a stop.\NYou do.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.52,0:33:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You come to a stop.\NAnd then the world can worry about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.05,0:34:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you topple over, you topple over, so...\NI feel like the spin of all that we have to do in this life
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.65,0:34:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is so distracting, and it's driving me crazy.\NDistracting from what?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.07,0:34:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Of what I want to just be.\NWell, what you are already is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.97,0:34:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NThis is a losing conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.73,0:34:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not mankind's birthright to trust in the universe,\Nand a very radical trust I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.22,0:34:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking about the celestial realm.\NYou're not talking about the physical realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.50,0:34:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm talking physical realm.\NIn the physical realm?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.86,0:34:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If I was in radical trust, I mean really radical trust,\Nlike I know the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.02,0:34:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what?\NIf you just...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.00,0:34:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I've done it.\NSo what happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.07,0:34:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That I don't have to try to create my physical self.\NYou don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.05,0:34:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're willing to sacrifice it,\Nsomething will come along,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.35,0:35:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will propagate the activity of the body,\Nor it won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.71,0:35:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's irrelevant.\NYou want it to be irrelevant, but still make it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.84,0:35:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhether you eat or not is the world's worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.70,0:35:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no interest in it.\NOkay, can I ask you,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.35,0:35:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,one more thing?\NI suffer kind of from a deep love of astrology.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.99,0:35:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You suffer from what?\NA deep love of astrology.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.75,0:35:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A deep love of astrology.\NOh, I thought a deep bad case of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.81,0:35:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI feel like I've been...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.67,0:35:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,loved astrology for lifetimes.\NI love the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.83,0:35:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I love the stars.\NI love the way they...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.97,0:35:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're stuck with the stars, yeah.\NGo ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.37,0:35:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I love the way they've guided me,\Nand...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.71,0:35:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, how come you got...\NI don't think I have any questions today.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.87,0:35:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I read your books,\Nand it put the seed of doubt, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.67,0:36:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,about the astral realms within me,\Nand I'm having difficulty...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.97,0:36:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I have difficulty making the break\Nbetween that paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.82,0:36:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and, I guess, just releasing it.\NThat astrology dominates your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.04,0:36:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Astrological influences?\NI think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.08,0:36:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Saturn's going over your back,\Nright, when Saturn is having lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.45,0:36:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and I feel like I give away my power,\Nbut at the same time, I feel...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.51,0:36:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you're giving away your power\Nto the immaterial, to the non-material,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.19,0:36:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to the physical.\NThe physical has no intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.19,0:36:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me how a whirling dirt ball\Ncan have intention about your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.03,0:36:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,love life.\NBecause I've seen...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.38,0:36:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not conscious.\NIt's dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.50,0:36:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a dirt ball.\NYou don't see the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.50,0:37:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness?\NThey're not...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.02,0:37:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You want me to ask?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.11,0:37:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThe physicality of a planet
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.29,0:37:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,has consciousness to resist.\NYou're projecting its power.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.04,0:37:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The only power it has\Nis what you project to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.04,0:37:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If you believe that this star\Nor this constellation
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.66,0:37:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,does what it does,\Nwhat happens if you disconnect
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.92,0:37:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,your belief from it?\NThen it's just a whirling dirt ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.90,0:37:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you put your faith in God?\NWell, I thought it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.99,0:37:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's not God.\NIt's the material, physical universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.48,0:37:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You're giving it the power,\Nfirst of all, of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.26,0:37:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We lectured about it today.\NThere is no this that can cause a that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.13,0:37:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your intention\Nthat a this should align with a that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.59,0:37:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like we said,\Nconsciousness of mankind evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.71,0:38:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time of the harmonic concordance.\NSo that which is all enveloping,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.04,0:38:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,including the physical universe,\Nis all in accord with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.26,0:38:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all in accord with each other\Nbecause it's all part of the one whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.58,0:38:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So the likelihood of something here\Nhappening in conformity
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.60,0:38:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,with this being here\Nis because they're both coming out
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.62,0:38:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of the same oneness,\Nnot because of this is causing a that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.74,0:38:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're separating it into a duality.\NThe universe is a unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.32,0:38:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So there would be the concordance\Nof that which is perhaps favorable
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.00,0:38:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time,\Nof the phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.36,0:38:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,not because this is causing that.\NUnderstand?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.32,0:38:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So the only mistake you're making is causality.\NThere is still likely a concordance,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.60,0:38:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,if for no other reason\Nthan the power you give it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.25,0:38:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,out of your own belief system.\NSo to exit a paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.52,0:39:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,do you just exit?\NYou transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.20,0:39:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to say it's wrong.\NI'm recontextualizing it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.60,0:39:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That the universe is part of the oneness\Nof the will of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.48,0:39:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's beyond causality.\NIt's beyond causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.06,0:39:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If I look at a hologram, see?\NIf I look at a hologram,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.82,0:39:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as I walk around the hologram,\Nit looks, what does it look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.04,0:39:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If I photograph it and speed it up,\Nit looks like there's a this causing a that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.80,0:39:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no this causing any that.\NThe only thing that's moved
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.23,0:39:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is my point of observation.\NSo it doesn't make any difference
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.30,0:39:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's these flowers\Nor an infinite world of plants
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.88,0:39:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or a planet swirling about each other.\NIt's still the same holographic phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.06,0:39:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,see, in which everything is part of the whole, see?\NOtherwise, you're trying to separate
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.43,0:39:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,this part of the hologram\Nfrom this part of the hologram
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.03,0:40:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and saying this is cause and this is effect.\NThat's all in your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.37,0:40:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I can switch it around and say no.\NIt's the other way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.07,0:40:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All I have to do is turn time backwards.\NDid Jesus teach that you get to heaven through astrology?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.96,0:40:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Answer me.\NDid he?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.30,0:40:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NDid the Buddha teach that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.70,0:40:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NDid Krishna teach that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.70,0:40:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NWho taught it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.34,0:40:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Some divine being?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.81,0:40:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand what she's saying,\Nbut you'll get caught up in an interest
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.42,0:40:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and put a lot of time and energy into it,\Nand I don't have a vested interest in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.42,0:40:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that it's wrong,\Nit's just that it's not contextualized correctly
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.90,0:40:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as part of the overall whole,\Nyou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.48,0:41:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NOn a lighter note,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.36,0:41:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a present for your cat.\NYou were calibrating cats
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.36,0:41:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for cat food last time,\Nand this is what I feed my cats,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.36,0:41:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't think you've ever heard\Nof this particular cat food.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.36,0:41:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good.\NYou might like to calibrate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.36,0:41:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called dead mice.\NA bag of dead mice.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.71,0:41:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, nice.\NOh, great.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.71,0:41:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.71,0:41:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOh, isn't that nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.29,0:41:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to try it.\NOh, this cat food calibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.29,0:41:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank God.\NMy cat has good karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.29,0:41:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if you bless food,\Nit jumps in calibration 10 to 15 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.29,0:41:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if you love your pet,\Nwhat you do is you feed your kitty
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.29,0:41:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,or your doggy or whatever,\Nyou bless this food
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.29,0:41:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of thy love, oh Lord,\Nbecause the dog's wagging tail is 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.29,0:42:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the kitty's purr is 500,\Nso you're just thanking God for their love.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.29,0:42:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I thank you for their love.\NYou bless their food,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.29,0:42:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're calibrated\Nto the level of the kitty food jumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.61,0:42:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was getting some pretty high numbers\Non this food,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.61,0:42:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and you said that most...\NI said it's over 200, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.61,0:42:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NMost cat food, you said,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.61,0:42:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't calibrate much.\NWell, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.61,0:42:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some big-selling brands\Nwhose names I don't want to mention
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.61,0:42:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in today's litiginous world.\NCalibrates below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.61,0:42:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know my cat pointed it out\Nbecause she wouldn't eat it,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.61,0:42:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,or you wouldn't eat it.\NAnd I was hoping to get a hug as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.61,0:42:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a dollar on me.\NShe doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.61,0:42:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NDid you give me kitty food?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.61,0:42:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NIt's around the flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.61,0:42:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.61,0:42:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the kitty food, dear.\NThank you for the kitty food.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.61,0:42:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know she'll love that.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.61,0:42:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We love it.\NWe love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.61,0:42:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me thank you for the kitty food.\NThat's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.74,0:42:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I thank you, my kitty food.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.74,0:42:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We all thank you.\NIn the name of the great kitty.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.74,0:42:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In the name of the great kitty,\Nwe do thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.90,0:43:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no question to ask.\NI ask you for a hug.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.90,0:43:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, a hug.\NI won't kick it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.90,0:43:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they want freebies.\NThank you, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.90,0:43:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThis mic is working okay, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.90,0:43:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.90,0:43:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NYes, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.12,0:43:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the same question.\NYou're into astrology, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.12,0:43:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.\NI once caught Venus in my backyard, dude, and you know what was Saturn, by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.73,0:43:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I reported it to the police, too.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.14,0:43:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.09,0:43:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.09,0:43:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.09,0:43:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.09,0:43:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.10,0:43:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.10,0:43:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.10,0:43:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.10,0:43:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.19,0:43:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I have a question I didn't have before.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.11,0:44:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When I first read your book, at the end, about the author, I wept, and the reason\Nbeing that you were talking about the energy flows that you had from your body, which I
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.26,0:44:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,have experienced from mine at times, and it just brought tears to my eyes.\NThat's the Kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.80,0:44:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,See, when we spoke, we didn't use that term today.\NI realize that's an omission of my part.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.04,0:44:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because over 200, what happens is the kundalini energy begins to flow.\NI wish it had a better name.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.70,0:44:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual energy, spiritual energy begins to flow.\NAnd that's what shifts you over to the processing a different thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.71,0:44:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the kundalini energy that actualizes the formation of the etheric brain.\NThe etheric brain is a consequence of the kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.19,0:44:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So an animal does not have an etheric brain.\NAlthough maybe cats and dogs do.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.77,0:44:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I never asked.\NI've had experiences where I felt it come all the way through my body, out my arm, out my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.99,0:45:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And one time I was sitting across from a lady and my hand was on her thigh and I went into her.\NAnd I lifted my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.29,0:45:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,She actually levitated.\NAnd I grumbled.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.83,0:45:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went to a parapsychology department at a university after that happened to ask them what possibly had happened.\NAnd all they said to me, well, we heard of this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.66,0:45:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at it as a love-giving experience.\NKundalini energy, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.74,0:45:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But to me what they were doing was just copying out.\NIt was not an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.80,0:45:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The kundalini energy, we didn't talk about that today, results in the so-called SIDDHAS.\NS-I-D-D-H-A-S.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.52,0:45:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Paranormal Phenomena.\NDistance viewing, clairaudience, clairvoyance, psychometry, you could grab this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.38,0:45:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I know who owned it, where it came from.\NI saw all of it's been spoken in the front of this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.14,0:46:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All those things are spontaneous.\NThe capacity to heal things, heal sicknesses, heal beings, the miraculous, all that is a consequence of that energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.77,0:46:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It does it of its own.\NWell, I know I didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.58,0:46:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it does it of its own.\NI don't know if that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.42,0:46:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll go next door and heal some crippled lady and she'll get up and walk away.\NIt's a big surprise, you know, it's a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.34,0:46:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Second question, please.\NSo it does all those things of its own, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.00,0:46:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NKnock on my microphone, you'll hear from my lawyer right into my teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.46,0:46:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,See, I can't talk that way anymore.\NHe's a perpetrator and I'm a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.34,0:46:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that.\NI got witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.12,0:46:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NDr. Hawkins, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.10,0:47:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the gift that you are to the world.\NMy question is, would you help me recontextualize the lower astral, the luciferic, the satanic?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.90,0:47:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYeah, the energies of the negative energies over the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.12,0:47:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucifer, you see, the luciferic is like about 190.\NIt's in our society.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.34,0:47:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's secular.\NIt wants to take God out of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.96,0:47:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause Lucifer did not want to acknowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.16,0:47:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The sovereignty of God.\NSo, therefore, it's a competition for power and prestige.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.05,0:47:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the luciferic that came to me as I went through the final pass.\NThe luciferic came to me as a knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.56,0:47:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you realize that you're beyond all answerability or consequence, beyond all karma,\Nall power is yours, own it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.47,0:47:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a temptation.\NIt's a temptation then, which comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.95,0:48:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the luciferic has to do with pride and power, prestige, and it distorts reason and logic via the distortions of the hermeneutics of relativistic epistemology.\NThat's where it invades the classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.15,0:48:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds very comical.\NBut, you know, the professorships of the universities have gone down, down, down right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.75,0:48:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The professors of six of the world's, United States greatest universities calibrate below 200.\NAnd a lot of the professors calibrate higher than the student body.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.53,0:48:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the sacrificing of truth, you know, for relativism.\NWhat is the problem with relativism?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.22,0:48:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It denies the reality of the absolute.\NIt's the Mad Hatter's Tea Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.68,0:49:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, a thing only means what I mean it to mean.\NThat denies, you see, the reality of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.08,0:49:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It says that I'm God.\NHow I see it and how I define it is how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.64,0:49:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, therefore, you can ridicule science and reason and logic and ethics and tradition.\NAnd now anything goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.13,0:49:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All morality and ethics are then hated constraints.\NAgainst freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.42,0:49:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom of what?\NFreedom of the id.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.42,0:49:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud's id.\NWhich seeks no accountability, answerability, or responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.90,0:50:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we see a society in which responsibility is now projected onto some supposedly evil external cause.\NMaking the Marxian dialectic error even more severe.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.62,0:50:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It is.\NTo begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.62,0:50:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, you see a downgrading of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.03,0:50:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it means that the way I see it is superior to truth.\NAnd that my way of seeing it is superior to all the greatest minds that have ever lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.48,0:50:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And that I am really superior to divinity.\NThat's a great game to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.07,0:50:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck.\NThe Lucifer.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.07,0:50:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the Lucifer.\NThe Satanic is represented by...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.49,0:50:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Torture, pain, and dynamiting busloads of children.\NI was hoping to find some way of finding humor in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.61,0:51:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to find humor in 300 kids being blown up.\NPerhaps the humor is in the absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.97,0:51:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The absurdity.\NBecause you're blowing up all these innocent children for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.97,0:51:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what makes it...\NSo, it's really more the ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.06,0:51:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,More the absurd.\NAnd it would be sad if it weren't so destructive.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.18,0:51:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.44,0:51:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the enemy is.\NThe enemy right now is that energy field which comes out of Wahhabism.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.44,0:51:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Wahhabism.\NThe tradition that I grew up in, and I'll be brief.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.66,0:51:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.17,0:51:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It is that the astral, the Satanic was so demonized, to put it that way,\Nthat people were afraid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.17,0:52:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we call it demonic, yes.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.17,0:52:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIf the energies get low enough, we call them demonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.17,0:52:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYou know, because they become homicidal.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.17,0:52:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.38,0:52:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Lower astral realms.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.38,0:52:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Dollar for a hug.\NAnd I'll come to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.38,0:52:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.61,0:52:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many domains, many realms.\NJust like...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.86,0:52:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't get into heaven today.\NBut...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.95,0:52:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll just say it to make sure that...\NBecause I don't want to...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.95,0:52:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The girl could not have said it.\NIf you stop breathing, you go...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.47,0:52:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I didn't say.\NNow I got to come back again to teach you what I didn't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.17,0:52:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I...\NThere are multiple heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.23,0:52:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't just one heaven.\NIt's a whole celestial realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.23,0:53:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Many religions are the sole pipeline to that region of heaven.\NSo when they claim exclusivity to heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.71,0:53:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,they are exclusive to that portion of heaven.\NWhich is that neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.71,0:53:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you got to have 30 wives in order to get into heaven,\Ntheir hunk of heaven, that's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.90,0:53:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,People only have one wife, you don't get admitted there.\NSo there are multiple heavens suitable for each set of belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.77,0:53:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the intentionality.\NDon't forget Krishna said,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.44,0:53:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,all who are devoted to me are dear to me.\NSo if you think God is in a pumpkin and you worship the pumpkin,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.44,0:53:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then there's...\NYou go to pumpkin heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.44,0:53:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to thank you.\NI feel so inspired when I hear you talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.52,0:53:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wish I could just be your apostle or something\Nand follow you around everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.52,0:53:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But my question is about the negative emotional states\Nbelow consciousness level 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.52,0:54:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI've heard those referred to as illusory or non-real or even non-existent.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.52,0:54:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they're based on misperception, yes.\NThey seem justified because that's how you're perceiving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.52,0:54:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, you're perceiving it that way\Nbecause that's what your level of consciousness is.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.52,0:54:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So the two reinforce each other.\NBut if they're non-existent,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.52,0:54:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,how can they still have an energy associated with it?\NWell, because perception determines what has no energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.87,0:54:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Those levels have energy.\NEach one has a justified level and energy, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.87,0:54:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If they have energy, then how can like imagination or something have energy?\NIf it's illusory, it's not real.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.51,0:54:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Like fear is not real.\NWell, not real in what sense depends on what you mean by real.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.51,0:54:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Real with a small R, real with a big R.\NThere's real with a big R in which none of this applies.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.38,0:54:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that why when you're over 600, nothing, test goes weak anymore?\NNot being weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.38,0:55:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're above consciousness level 600, you don't go weak anymore with kinesiology?\NNo, nothing makes you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.76,0:55:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So those negative emotional states,\Nyou realize that they are fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.76,0:55:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception.\NYou realize they are perception, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.76,0:55:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But that perception creates its own reality within its own energy field.\NHatred is hatred and it does have its own energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.11,0:55:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see that the basis of the hatred is illusion.\NWe gave you a way out of hatred today forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.40,0:55:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates, when he said that every man chooses only the good,\Nright away you got, oh, that's the tool, the understanding I needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.66,0:55:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I can forgive everyone.\NThey choose only the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.07,0:55:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They blow up a whole lot of children because that to them is the good.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.07,0:55:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI'm getting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.07,0:55:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm signing this.\NIt's a quarter after four.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.07,0:55:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how many people are here.\NDon't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.07,0:55:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.\NI'll worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.07,0:56:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NLet God worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.07,0:56:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,God's problem, not my problem.\NI don't run this universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.07,0:56:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't run this universe.\NI'm telling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.97,0:56:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNo, I'm glad you reminded me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.97,0:56:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you.\NDr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.97,0:56:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NToday you mentioned that there are a number of mantras that calibrate in the 700s.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.00,0:56:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's also my understanding that for the past 2,000, 3,000 years and up until today,\Nthat the majority of enlightened beings have come from the Eastern religions, primarily Buddhism,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.00,0:56:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which seems to have a predominant practice of using mantras.\NAnd it's not due to the mantras.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.03,0:56:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The mantra is an expression of the intention.\NAnd the reason Buddhism is so effective is because it looks for divinity within.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.74,0:57:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,See, in the Western world, God is pictured and held by belief systems to be transcendent,\Nout there, somewhere ahead in time or behind in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.96,0:57:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Created the universe, disappeared.\NNow you're going to meet the big man over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.57,0:57:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NSo God is pictured as transcendent.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.63,0:57:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Eastern understanding, Hindu and Aryan, East Indian and Buddhic, the God is imminent.\NSo it is the imminent God within as the Self, with a capital S, as the source of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.39,0:57:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which one experiences in the divine state is the unmanifest becoming manifest as your existence.\NThe source of joy is the awareness of the source of your existence, which is ever-present.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.39,0:58:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When I say thee, O Lord, I'm speaking to that which is already present,\Nnot something in the future or something in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.40,0:58:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NIt was discovered when you let go of the barriers, when you let go of duality,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.74,0:58:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the reality shines forth as self-realization.\NIt does so spontaneously of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.25,0:58:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because you caused it, but because when the clouds are removed, the sun shines forth.\NBut you didn't cause the sun to shine forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.44,0:58:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, I just wanted to thank you.\NI do have a question, but I first wanted to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.55,0:58:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the one that, and Lou and Shelly helped me out of this call group.\NAnd you gave me some suggestions last time I spoke to join an Al-Anon group, which I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.55,0:58:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NAnd things are moving along.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.55,0:58:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm learning to let go and let God.\NAnd just feeling the flow of God just working through me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.55,0:59:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You took my advice?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.55,0:59:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I am going to leave the world.\NEverybody has it. Few people take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.58,0:59:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So do I get $20 in?\NNo, you get a dollar for taking my advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.65,0:59:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, my question is, it deals with undoing karma.\NAnd I know you mentioned, you talked about it briefly in another question.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.65,0:59:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides becoming the field and maybe surrendering our will to God,\Nis there specific things, like if we would ask, God, is there karma that I can get rid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.74,0:59:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And what could I do to precipitate that?\NOr does it just come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.74,0:59:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it shows up of its own.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.74,1:00:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to hustle it up.\NAlthough spiritual work often results in your life becoming chaotic for a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.06,1:00:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Because spiritual work then begins removing the karmic layers and you move rapidly.\NOkay. Great.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.61,1:00:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes people think their life is getting worse.\NIt's not getting worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.02,1:00:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that they're moving it ahead faster.\NMoving it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.02,1:00:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And people go into beatific states and then it doesn't last.\NAnd they feel very sad about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.06,1:00:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because they've transcended their karma for up to now.\NAnd then the next layer of what needs to be undone becomes undone.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.06,1:00:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But the flashes of beauty and inner light are presaging.\NThey tell you that you're in the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.12,1:00:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Just keep going.\NJust keep going.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.12,1:00:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you undo that next bunch of negative karma, it comes back again.\NSo it's recurrent.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.12,1:00:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.12,1:01:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I have a hug, too?\NYou can have a hug.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.46,1:01:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who takes my advice deserves a hug.\NHi, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.14,1:01:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI had a question about this old book that I found.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.14,1:01:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called The Life and Teachings of the Great Masters of the Far East.\NYeah, it's a famous book.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.14,1:01:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was just wondering, my question was, have you ever read it?\NHandle or calibrate it?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.14,1:01:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.\NI'm very familiar with it, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.14,1:01:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NOK.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.72,1:01:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.72,1:01:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.\NThat was all I had.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.61,1:01:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThe book calibrates over 500 verses.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.61,1:01:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,550, 560, 580, 575, 560, 565, 560.\NCan I raise the 560?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.61,1:01:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NGood evening, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.61,1:01:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the wonderful enlightenment that you've given us.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.70,1:01:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.80,1:01:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.80,1:01:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.80,1:01:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.44,1:01:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.44,1:01:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.44,1:01:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.44,1:02:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I messed up.\NDo you think I got a hand?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.44,1:02:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my first time, my first exposure.\NWhere are you, arm?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.44,1:02:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are your...\NI had my first exposure to yourي
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.76,1:02:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.86,1:02:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N300, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.86,1:02:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You've recovered, though, you've recovered from it pretty well.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.86,1:02:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They call me the Bill O'Reilly of spirituality, you know.\Nmy husband and I and soon after we had him we realized that there were things
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.24,1:02:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that were not just right with him so when he started school we were having\Nproblems and eventually he's now 37 he has been diagnosed as bipolar borderline
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.72,1:02:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have stuck by him and we will continue to do that but I was wondering\Nif there was it's been very draining on us and yet we don't want to abandon what
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.52,1:03:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we started I mean we were told by a pediatrician way in the beginning that\Nwe could probably give him up because he was suspecting something might be wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.70,1:03:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with him because of his biological mother yes and we decided that we would\Nnot do that so that was our decision to keep him and we bonded and of course I
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.70,1:03:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,bonded with him within five minutes when they gave him to me\Nyou're welcome
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.58,1:03:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're still suffering he's 37 he's he finally left the United States he's\Nliving in New Zealand now but still very very dependent on us because he's never
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.05,1:03:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,been able to work he's very brilliant but he doesn't have any judgmental with\Nhim to control his or to regulate his daily activities and he's chronically
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.83,1:03:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,disabled yes yeah so I was wondering I mean I know that was kind of a far-out\Nquestion but
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.33,1:04:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is there anything that can be done on a miraculous or a spiritual level I mean\Nwe've tried my husband and I you know we've we've done a lot of reading we've
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.63,1:04:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,done a lot of growing in the last 37 years well you then you'd let go on to change him no we\Ndon't want to change him we can't all right so what is the problem the problem
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.63,1:04:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is how do we I mean we've gotten to the point where we are so exhausted now you\Nmust be resisting that otherwise you're not exhausted you're exhausted from what
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.33,1:04:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.33,1:04:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.32,1:04:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.32,1:04:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.32,1:04:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.32,1:04:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.61,1:04:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.61,1:04:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.61,1:04:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.94,1:04:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.94,1:04:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.22,1:04:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.93,1:04:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.93,1:04:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.93,1:05:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\Nexhausted from what?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.97,1:05:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,exhausted from what?\NTo accept what is, then let go, wind it, change it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.51,1:05:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the prayer you need.\NWe can't. We realize that there's nothing we can do.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.15,1:05:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's an intellectual. You haven't accepted it.\NAcceptance, it's neither this nor that.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.69,1:05:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It just is that way.\NMy kitty is orange.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.16,1:05:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I just accept it's orange.\NI don't want to make it black. I don't want to make it gray.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.04,1:05:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't grieve the fact that it's orange.\NI just let it be what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.54,1:05:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So you let your son be what it is, like a kitty cat.\NBut don't give me any buts.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.65,1:05:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Just do what I tell you.\NTake the first step in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.61,1:05:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI told you that.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.86,1:05:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the first step in it.\NIt's all step groups have that.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.44,1:05:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,First step, you admit that your power was sober.\NStop trying to change it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.71,1:06:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The context for my question is that I have\Na spiritual healing practice where I work with people
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.55,1:06:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to help them.\NThey experience or become aware of the presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.23,1:06:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And on a few occasions, it seems that I have helped someone\Nwho is more spiritually advanced than myself
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.53,1:06:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to higher levels than they've ever attained before.\NYet there's a traditional belief that a master can't take a student
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.62,1:06:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond his own level.\NWho said you're a master?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.04,1:06:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, but is it possible for me or for anyone\Nto help someone go beyond their own level?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.08,1:06:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.\NYou can give a person a book.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.92,1:06:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And they become enlightened as a result of applying it.\NSo you're only a stepping stone, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.18,1:06:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A stepping stone.\NIt's the intention of the other person, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.96,1:06:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention of the other person\Nwill activate a single sentence.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.68,1:07:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And all you needed was that one sentence to shoot through.\NBut it's their intention that activates that sentence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.41,1:07:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't do it.\NYou don't do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.81,1:07:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a facilitator.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.06,1:07:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You carry the message, but not the person.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.92,1:07:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's not.\NIt's up to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.92,1:07:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You give them the message.\NIt could be 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.92,1:07:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One morning they wake up and they say, oh, Zowie.\NMan chooses only the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.92,1:07:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NWhen I'm working.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.92,1:07:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I said that today, didn't I?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.92,1:07:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates told me that a long time ago.\NSocrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.92,1:07:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When I'm working with them, I'm praying that they receive a healing and a teaching.\NAnd they often later come back and say, you know, after I left, it occurred to me that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.92,1:07:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think, okay, that's the teaching.\NAnd I know it didn't come through me.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.92,1:07:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo you put in your ore.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.92,1:07:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd that's all you can do, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.92,1:07:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThe rest is up to the other person and their acceptance and their karma, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.92,1:07:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing is the truth.\NThe other thing is acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.92,1:07:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHi, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.10,1:07:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI have a question about your.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.10,1:07:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You made a comment earlier this year in one of your videos that I saw about your orange\Nkitty.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.10,1:08:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You said it was the only one in the universe.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.32,1:08:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And my question is, is there just one human being in the universe?\NNow, it's there over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.31,1:08:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200, you have individual karma.\NYou have an etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.31,1:08:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You have responsibility for your choices and your actions.\NAnd the animal kingdom has one central consciousness that radiates out in multiple bodies so that
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.40,1:08:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you meet one orange kitty, you've met them all in a way, you know.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.24,1:08:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NCan I have a hug?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.24,1:08:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.24,1:08:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You got an orange kitty in there?\NYou got kitty food?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.24,1:08:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.24,1:08:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NBoy, I'm making big money today.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.24,1:09:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My question, Dr. Hawkins, is would eating raw food benefit the body and nervous system\Nfor the Kundalini energy to come up through?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.52,1:09:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it prepare it better?\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.45,1:09:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If eating raw food would prepare the body…\NI don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.45,1:09:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NI don't think it has anything to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.45,1:09:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NIt doesn't have anything to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.55,1:09:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NBecause it's non-linear, non-physical.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.55,1:09:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a non-linear, non-physical energy.\NTherefore, I don't think physical manipulations have any influence on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.55,1:09:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,On whether the energy comes up easily or…\NI don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.55,1:09:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,…whatever.\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.55,1:09:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when it's ready to come up, it comes up by itself.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.55,1:09:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And when it's not ready, you know, I don't believe in trying to promote it artificially,\Nbecause then it's not real, it's not you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.68,1:10:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.71,1:10:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes about automatically.\NAs you become more loving towards all of life and all of the expressions, then it begins
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.71,1:10:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to flow automatically of its own.\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.71,1:10:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NI understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.79,1:10:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.79,1:10:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you so much for answering that.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.79,1:10:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd I would like to have a hug, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.79,1:10:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.91,1:10:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NWe have to be out of here at 5 in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.91,1:10:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Half hour, we've got…\NOkay, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.61,1:10:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll make it.\NWe'll make it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.61,1:10:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That was my mother, by the way.\NI know we'll make it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.61,1:10:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll always make it.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.61,1:10:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NDo you guys always calibrate the group consciousness before and after?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.96,1:10:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you done that?\NOr do you stop doing that?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.96,1:10:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We usually do it, you know.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.96,1:10:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.96,1:10:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you be interested in doing that today?\NWell, let's see what the consciousness level of the audience did today.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.96,1:10:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness…\NWe have permission to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.96,1:11:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the group here, the consciousness level of the group, from the beginning to the end\Nof the lecture, it went up over 8 points, 9 points, 10 points, 11 points, about 10, 11
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.73,1:11:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,points.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.73,1:11:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That wasn't my question.\NIt just occurred to me on the way up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.73,1:11:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NNo, that's because…
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.37,1:11:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he's got another question.\NHe spent a dollar already.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.40,1:11:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NGo ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.85,1:11:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo this is studying someone who has quit eating.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.85,1:11:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've been a student of that subject for quite some time.\NWhat subject?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.85,1:11:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, some people call it breatharianism, but there are people that are spontaneously\Nnot eating in China.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.85,1:11:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, breatharians.\NYes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.85,1:11:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And they give them a whole different label, and they don't even know the term.\NBut I'm wondering, you know, because a lot of these people that are doing this happen
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.85,1:11:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to be spiritual-oriented.\NI don't know if there's a connection between the two, but here's my question, because I'm
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.85,1:12:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to pull together some material on the subject of health, and I'm going to make\Na brief mention of breatharianism.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.85,1:12:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want to know whether you have to have a certain calibrated level of consciousness\Nin order for that to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.85,1:12:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm not necessarily connecting it with spirituality.\NI just want to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.85,1:12:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like, based on paying attention to your research, that it has to be at least\N200.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.85,1:12:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there something...\NThere aren't too many breatharians around.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.11,1:12:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, like I said, NASA's got one, and they're studying them for the obvious reason.\NIs it possible for you to find out if...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.24,1:12:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you tired of eating?\NWhat is your problem?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.24,1:12:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You can stop eating any time you want.\NOh, I can?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.24,1:12:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.24,1:12:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.78,1:13:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a calibrated level of consciousness that you have to reach?\NI never calibrated it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.78,1:13:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NI never did research it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.78,1:13:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NI think we asked about one.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.78,1:13:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me hold in mind something.\NThe one I'm holding in mind is genuine.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.91,1:13:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a genuine one in Germany.\NThat's the only one I know about.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.91,1:13:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Woman.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.91,1:13:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So is it possible to ask if there's a calibrated level of consciousness in order to...\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.91,1:13:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have time to research it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.91,1:13:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be too much time.\NI have more than one question.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.91,1:13:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd could you see whether this book is integrous or not just by the Kinesian?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.91,1:13:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.91,1:13:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you much.\NWe're tough.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.91,1:13:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NStop eating.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.35,1:13:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's easy.\NStop breathing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.35,1:13:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Try that one.\NThat way you transcend the body quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.35,1:13:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit eating.\NIt takes a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.35,1:13:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit breathing.\NInstant karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.35,1:13:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.35,1:13:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.35,1:13:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.65,1:13:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.65,1:13:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NInstant karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.68,1:13:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we are.\NDr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.68,1:14:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAre you familiar with Thomas Hora that wrote Beyond a Dream?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.68,1:14:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NI was learning to...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.68,1:14:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of authors I'm not familiar with are multitudinous.\NCould you calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.68,1:14:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?\NBeyond...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.88,1:14:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas Hora?\NBeyond a Dream?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.88,1:14:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.88,1:14:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How about Joel Goldsmith?\NWe only calibrated people that calibrated 460 and over.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.88,1:14:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.88,1:14:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.88,1:14:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.88,1:14:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.36,1:14:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.36,1:14:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.36,1:14:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.36,1:14:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Joel Goldsmith was over 460, yes.\NForty-five, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.36,1:14:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He was, still.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.36,1:14:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The only other thing I'd mention is, on a personal level, it seems like...\NI don't know if I'm getting old or silly or what, but, I tear up so easily.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.48,1:14:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Tear up?\NTear up.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.48,1:14:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Tear up.\NTear up.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.48,1:14:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIs this a symptom of me becoming more spiritual, or just a silly old lady?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.22,1:14:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.22,1:14:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, we'd have to research it individually.\NYou tear up with what? Joy or sadness?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.26,1:15:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no, anything that moves me.\NYeah, no, that's just, that's very common.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.58,1:15:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do spiritual work, you find yourself crying all the time.\NOh, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.84,1:15:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a certain level in which the slightest sign of love or tenderness or something, you just weep.\NAnd when you go through it, it's sort of tough.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.16,1:15:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in an airport waiting for a plane.\NAnd you see this wife look at her husband, and you can just see the love.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.38,1:15:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And you just break out in tears about it.\NOh, well, that's comforting because my grown children just tease me.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.76,1:15:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, are you going to cry now?\NIn monasteries, it's, you know, well-known.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.32,1:15:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And people often cry for several years.\NThey hit a certain level of love, and they cry sometimes for a couple years.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.46,1:15:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's incredible.\NI'm going to cry for a couple years.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.09,1:16:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Invest in Kleenex and be with it.\NYeah, well, at least we're not going in the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.32,1:16:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, beauty makes you weep, beautiful music.\NThe most common experience of it is beautiful music.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.90,1:16:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you hear the introduction to Lohengrin or Tannhäuser.\NAnd as you hear the music mount, Jesus, God, it just wipes you off.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.42,1:16:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, anything of great beauty just wipes you out.\NSo be prepared to be wiped out pretty often.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.82,1:16:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Or avoid the beautiful.\NExcept that everything in the world considers ugly.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.64,1:16:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it's innate beauty, so you can't escape it either.\NOkay, you know, that's the phase you go through.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.30,1:16:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, doctor.\NMay I have a hug?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.42,1:17:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NIf you don't cry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.58,1:17:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.\NYes, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.08,1:17:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a beautiful state you're in.\NLove it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.36,1:17:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, don't sit down.\NI'll save you the time of sitting down.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.60,1:17:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.76,1:17:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NDr. Oggins, thank you very much for your work.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.32,1:17:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted to ask you if you might illustrate the kinesthological method for me.\NYou didn't see it today?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.40,1:17:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw you do it with her, but I don't know how to do it myself.\NYou can't do it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.94,1:17:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to have a partner the way I do it.\NThere is a way of doing it by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.44,1:17:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When were you?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.44,1:17:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that reliable.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.63,1:17:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I try it with you?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.84,1:17:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because nothing makes me go weak.\NYou see, I hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.86,1:17:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't tell her what I'm thinking.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.08,1:17:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding in mind calibrates over 900 resists, 950 resists, 975 resists, 980\Nresists, 990 resists.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.08,1:18:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWhat I'm holding in mind calibrates over 900 resists, 950 resists, 975 resists, 980
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.24,1:18:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,resists, 990 resists, 980 resists, 980 resists, 980 resists, 980 resists, 980 resists, 980 resists,\N990 resists, 980 resists, 980 resists, 980 resists.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.24,1:18:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding in mind calibrates over 1000 resists.\NNow, I didn't tell her what I was holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.44,1:18:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth makes the body go strong quickly.\NBut it's a very fast response.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.44,1:18:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you hold something in mind and you press down with two fingers, the person resists\Nto the same degree as you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.22,1:18:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\Nthat you're pressing down.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.50,1:18:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The reaction is very quick, see?\NSo you can't hold a thing in mind and press down,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.55,1:18:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, wait a minute, and then press down.\NBecause it'll create a doubt in your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.63,1:18:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,if you verbalize it, I suggest you do it non-verbally.\NOtherwise, you may come back later with a doubt,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.63,1:19:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,well, it's because of what I said, the person heard me, see?\NDon't tell them what you're holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.06,1:19:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hold a famous painting in mind,\Nand I say, now, what I'm, let's see,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.82,1:19:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,there was recently a rediscovery of a great painter,\Nabout a year or two ago, what was that great painting
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.62,1:19:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that he rediscovered, one of the greatest masters\Nof all time, and the argument was
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.80,1:19:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it was legitimate or not.\NSo Van Gogh, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.26,1:19:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.94,1:19:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It started with an R, wasn't it?\NOne of the greatest, like Titian or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.82,1:19:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the question was whether it was legitimate or not,\Nso just for curiosity, yeah, we asked,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.06,1:19:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is it legitimate or not, and it is, it is, mm-hmm.\NTrying to think of the name of the artist,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.74,1:20:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the greatest names in art.\NIt was Ramiro, I think it was Ramiro.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.84,1:20:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember now.\NAnyway, it's worth multi-millions of dollars,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.60,1:20:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so to be able to tell whether it's false or not false.\NAt home, I have a Picasso that makes you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.26,1:20:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We hung it in the bathroom.\NIt's a fake Picasso.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.37,1:20:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my own question.\NI'd just like a hug, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.23,1:20:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, uh-oh.\NI'm going to go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.40,1:20:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm getting away easy today, no chowky talk.\NI'll just hug you here.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.02,1:20:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So yes, who was that great artist?\NOh, god.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.48,1:20:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it called?\NOne of the greatest.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.80,1:20:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it a Vermeer?\NI think it was Vermeer, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.28,1:21:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me just ask again.\NWhat I'm holding in mind calibrates over 700, 750, 780.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.95,1:21:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That Vermeer calibrated around 750.\NThe world's greatest art experts have a great deal
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.40,1:21:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of difficulty deciding whether a piece of art is legitimate\Nor not.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.30,1:21:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We can tell in a second.\NMy question is, from a spiritual perspective
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.01,1:21:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the long run, does it really\Nmatter who wins the upcoming presidential election?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.65,1:21:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In the long, in the greater context, no.\NIn the greater context, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.58,1:21:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause it's the unfolding of the collective karma
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.92,1:21:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind in its expression in the United States\Nat this particular time and under these circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.85,1:21:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me just ask a question myself.\NOK, the intention of the person I'm holding in mind is over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.35,1:21:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention of the person I'm holding in mind is over 200.\NThe intention of both.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.77,1:21:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Both contestants is integrous.\NThey both intend.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.87,1:22:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They both have integrous intention.\NSo I'm worried about a person's intention, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.30,1:22:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If a person's intention is integrous,\Nthen I'll lend them my car, if it's not at all, I'd say.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.85,1:22:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I once lent my car to somebody, and I didn't calibrate him.\NI had to go get it myself several weeks later.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.85,1:22:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sitting in his driveway with the key in it out of gas.\NHi, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.00,1:22:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.\NQuestion from the last lecture I went to in this one
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.22,1:22:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is that in order to raise consciousness,\Nyou would embrace the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.08,1:22:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the best ways to do that\Nis to pick something that's truly sacred.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.48,1:22:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Love, beauty, forgiveness, really embrace that.\NCould you elaborate a little bit more on that,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.41,1:22:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and then maybe how you can really get into that in light\Nof maybe some of our occupations, daily challenges,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.13,1:23:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,things like that?\NTo be one with the field, then, is
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.24,1:23:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,like being with the current moment in a generality\Nrather than a specificity.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.79,1:23:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, say, the upcoming election.\NWhat are you concerned about?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.25,1:23:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm concerned about whether the people are integrous, right?\NNow we ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.32,1:23:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You could then ask.\NWhat is for the highest good of the country?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.74,1:23:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what is for the highest good of mankind, et cetera?\NYour alignment with integrity then tends to bring it to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.75,1:23:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,To see the sacredness of all that exists is a revelation.\NIt's not something you can will or program.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.95,1:24:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It reveals itself spontaneously.\NYou're walking through the woods,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.68,1:24:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly you see the stunning perfection of one\Nthing standing out in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.91,1:24:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You wonder, God.\NIt's God revealing the divinity which
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.74,1:24:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is present in all of creation.\NAnd it's a revelation when you remove the obstacles to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.93,1:24:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And the obstacles are dualistic perception.\NSo the reason we talk about nonlinear reality
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.26,1:24:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is because it's the fastest pathway.\NIf I stop and say the flowers are beautiful or not beautiful,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.72,1:24:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have to name every flower, I'm really missing what they are.\NWhat are they?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.16,1:24:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They're obviously somebody's intention to create beauty\Nand to uplift the audience, to uplift.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.86,1:25:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever put this together did so in the name of beauty, you see?\NSo you see the intention of the flowers and their arrangement
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.34,1:25:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and their being here is, in a way, worshipful of beauty,\Nexpression of the worship.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.76,1:25:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NOf beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.04,1:25:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So you begin to see the beauty of all that exists.\NIt's a matter of just becoming aware and sensitive to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.42,1:25:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All things that exist are intrinsically beautiful.\NAnd I'd like a hug.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.28,1:25:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NSo much.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.54,1:25:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk through an alley, and all of a sudden,\Nthe alley and everything in it, all the garbage cans,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.48,1:25:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,strike you as an impressionistic painting.\NIncredible.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.89,1:25:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a stage set.\NNext time you see something the world calls ugly,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.10,1:26:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,look at it as a stage set.\NEverything is a stage set.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.73,1:26:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk through the alley, there's the tin can,\Nthere's the kitty climbing on the tin can,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.63,1:26:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the little rats scurrying all around.\NI mean, it's a perfect stage set.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.59,1:26:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see it?\NThe theatrics of the presents itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.32,1:26:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you see through our artistic eyes,\Nyou'll see the intrinsic beauty of the garbage can.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.16,1:26:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I love old garbage cans.\NI mean, they just, whoa, they're so droopy.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.16,1:26:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And this little rat runs up the side,\Nand you run down the other side.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.20,1:26:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's like the theater.\NTheater, it's like theater.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.52,1:26:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You see all of existence like theater.\NI mean, the politicians getting out there and .
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.33,1:26:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like fantastic theater, you know what I mean?\NThe ones that were up a couple of months ago
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.05,1:27:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,shaving their fists.\NIt's hysterical, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.40,1:27:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All the fish shaking.\NYou calibrate them, 135, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.00,1:27:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins.\NThank you very much for your presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.92,1:27:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very grateful.\NI want to ask you something about the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.40,1:27:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,anatta and individual karma, the anatta doctrine of no mind.\NAnd I think that I'm having problems with this
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.32,1:27:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because our language in subject predicate fashion\Nis naturally dualistic and the semantic difficulty.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.68,1:27:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But who actually changes the program in that DVD\Nthat has an end during his life in our life's journey?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.30,1:27:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is no actual I that has a substantial essence,\Nhow can we affect our own spiritual advancement?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.16,1:27:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we become?\NWho has?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.84,1:27:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Who has free will?\NWho is it that no individual I is needed?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.90,1:27:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it?\NYou know, how does karma?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.40,1:27:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a composition you're reading me.\NYou're not asking me a question.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.32,1:28:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm just trying to qualify all these things.\NI'm going to give you a D on the presentation so far.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.20,1:28:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, how?\NYeah, I want you to cut to the quick of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.44,1:28:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we have individual karma if it happens at 200\Nand we have a, you know, an etheric brain?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.16,1:28:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you have a collective karma up to 200,\Nsuch as the animals do.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.71,1:28:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when you transcend consciousness level 200,\Nyou, for the first time, come into spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.54,1:28:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and spiritual power.\NFrom that point on, you have an individual consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.52,1:28:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,individual consciousness.\NUp to that time, you share the collective.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.30,1:28:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You share the collective.\NSee, one forgiving thought can take you right out
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.98,1:28:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of that field, one forgiving thought.\NIt all takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.38,1:28:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you actually remembered your karma as a tiger?\NOr was that a joke?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.19,1:29:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The tigerness, I subjectively intuit.\NI don't remember being a tiger.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.35,1:29:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But many lifetimes, you do remember.\NAnd because they were highly significant
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.31,1:29:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,from a spiritual viewpoint and beyond a certain level,\Nyou consciously remember them in excruciating detail,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.46,1:29:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,unfortunately.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.16,1:29:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember them, yeah.\NIf the individual I does not exist as a substantial essence,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.28,1:29:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,how do we not remember a lot of different?\NYou're getting into a lot of languaging now.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.70,1:29:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just kind of.\NNo, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.78,1:29:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my problem.\NWhat are you really asking?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.23,1:29:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I was raised Roman Catholic.\NAnd I studied philosophy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.91,1:29:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And my problem is the no mind and who reincarnates.\NYou're mixing levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.25,1:29:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not making any sense.\NRight, that's what I figured.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.89,1:29:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's apples and oranges, right?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.03,1:29:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, thank you very much.\NCan I have a hug?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.25,1:29:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What reincarnates.\NWhat reincarnates.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.13,1:30:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What reincarnates is that which thinks it has a mind.\NThat which is nonlinear doesn't reincarnate,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.05,1:30:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because it never incarnated.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.27,1:30:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish we had more time to answer him thoroughly.\NWell, it would take longer to decipher and translate it
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.36,1:30:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,into language.\NBecause this one goes to the satellite room
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.98,1:30:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and this one is here.\NSo we have to speak to both of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.24,1:30:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot the satellite room.\NI didn't even remember when I say a lot of the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.52,1:30:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NGuilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.40,1:30:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt?\NWell, tell them to come in here and say hello to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.68,1:30:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NWell, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.14,1:30:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.\NI'm a facilitator.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.34,1:30:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm naturally grabbing the mic.\NCan you tell me what the relationship is
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.70,1:30:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,between a sudden change in our level of consciousness\Nand the rate of divorces that are happening
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.98,1:30:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,or breakup of relationships, specifically\Nlong-term relationships?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.04,1:31:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I think there's a relationship\Nbetween the collective consciousness level and the level
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.54,1:31:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own consciousness?\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.66,1:31:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Break up of relationships? Is that what you're asking?\NYes, the increase of our conscious level.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.92,1:31:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I never asked the question. I never researched it.\NDoes it have anything to do with the indigo children?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.81,1:31:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NOkay, thank you. May I have a hug?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.06,1:31:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,People may stay together because they're evolved or because they're not evolved.\NOr one or the other, or more evolved than the others.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.12,1:31:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Too dumb to know about it, right?\NOr too smart to change my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.60,1:31:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I had two questions.\NOne, would you take a picture with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.82,1:31:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.\NAnd the other, something that I would call a discrepancy,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.28,1:32:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm sure there's an explanation.\NYou had two calibrations for Descartes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.38,1:32:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One in Power vs. Force, $4.99.\NNo, no, Descartes is not $4.99.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.52,1:32:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NDescartes is around $4.60.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.37,1:32:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Descartes is around $4.60, yeah.\NDescartes is around $4.60.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.08,1:32:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Descartes is around $4.60, I think.\N$4.60, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.22,1:32:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Einstein is $4.99.\NDescartes is, no, Descartes is differentiated between res interna and res externa.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.79,1:32:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So that would be around $4.50, $4.55.\NLook at this.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.02,1:32:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He's two of me.\NLet me shake your hand, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.07,1:33:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not tall.\NI'm a midget that explains it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.69,1:33:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They called me shorty, so it's not that he's tall, it's that I'm short, yes.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.60,1:33:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my first time to see you, and I just finished Power vs. Force.\NSo my question is on kinesiology for beginners.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.88,1:33:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we just keep continuing to practice to be able to really do it as effectively as you're doing it?\NWell, don't forget we have a lot of practice.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.24,1:33:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou can tell, you can, there's a lot of people you can study with on the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.88,1:33:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There's people who do kinesiology, teach kinesiology all over the country.\NIn fact, there are always keeps a list of them, and when we speak around, we often meet teachers of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.48,1:33:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very, very simple.\NIt's based somewhat on a sensitivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.91,1:34:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, I can ask a question, and she'll already feel the energy of the answer run down her,\Nher arm, before the muscles react.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.38,1:34:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I've gotten so sensitive that I can experience the energy that is running down her arm.\NAnd I already got the answer before her arm does one thing or the other.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.44,1:34:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But we've been doing it together for.\NFor instance, if I ask if Descartes over 460, I already feel the positive energy out.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.24,1:34:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Descartes are on 460.\NSo it's clear that this is the basis of knowing the truth to the false for all of those that don't have this, or for me,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.66,1:34:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we just continue to practice.\NYou're saying there are people.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.06,1:34:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have anybody that you recommend for teaching?\NThere are teachers all over the country and and most chiropractors know how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.74,1:34:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Most holistic practitioners of medicine know how to do it.\NThere are study groups that study this work here all over the country that do it routinely.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.15,1:34:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we just started a study group on this in Denver.\NSo we're just beginning, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.73,1:35:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we're trying to fine tune our skills.\NSo.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.49,1:35:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.\NOK.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.63,1:35:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Going and doing something like.\NWell, we intend to do a teaching video on kinesiology, but we're bored with kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.93,1:35:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So we never did do it.\NBut if kinesiology is the basis for us to know truth, then we would need to learn it to be able to.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.87,1:35:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way to verify truth.\NRight. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.01,1:35:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see what's happened to her arm.\NShe used to be useful, but she's not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.23,1:35:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, great.\NYeah, as I say, it's like writing a bicycle.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.67,1:35:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll know why after the new book comes out, if you want.\NAnyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.75,1:35:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.\NWhen you get where it's at, you've got it, you know, and it's just sort of getting the space of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.99,1:35:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.\NAnd if you're around people that know how to do it or do it all the time, you sort of pick it up intuitively from them, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.51,1:35:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.82,1:35:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NAnd can I have a hug, too?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.18,1:35:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo you can't have a vested interest in the answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.87,1:36:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to ask a question in the name of the highest good.\NFor instance, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.49,1:36:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Between the two contestants for the presidency, I'm only interested in whether they have integrity or not.\NIf one of them makes your arm go weak, then that would not be for the highest good of the country.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.01,1:36:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got nothing to do with who they are, you know.\NI mean, they all went to Ivy League colleges, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.25,1:36:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYou're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.25,1:36:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes.\NFirst of all, Lily Tomlin's bag lady tests, reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.23,1:36:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing more than a collective hunch.\NLily Tomlin, I love her, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.51,1:36:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Me, too.\NYou know, to humor is one of the pathways to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.43,1:36:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought it would be too comical to write a book about it, so.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.62,1:37:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because forgiveness, you see, is innate to humor.\NAnd if you calibrate, we, in fact, for the book we did, we calibrated all the most best-known humorists, the
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.40,1:37:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,most recent times.\NThey're all around 480 or so, very erudite.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.78,1:37:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All the best-known humorists calibrate, you know, 460, 475, 480.\NAnd there's something disarming about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.68,1:37:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I think humor is one of the best ways of learning and teaching, and one of the best ways to\Nexperience yourself, because if you take yourself humorously, nobody can get you there.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.80,1:37:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you realize you're stupid and ugly, it's...\NYou're way ahead of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.23,1:37:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What can they say?\NMy question is on a personal note.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.40,1:37:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What is blocking me from manifesting my full abilities as a manual therapist?\NAs a what?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.66,1:37:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Manual therapist.\NI'm a physical therapist.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.66,1:37:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What's blocking your talents?\NNothing's blocking your talents.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.66,1:38:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you think something's blocking your talents?\NClasses that I take, advanced classwork, I'm often able to manifest picking up restrictions
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.22,1:38:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and doing the techniques, but in my own clinic, I'm lacking.\NI feel lacking.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.22,1:38:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NThat's a personal, investigative matter we'd have to go into, I don't know why.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.99,1:38:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you may have to do self-confidence or your role, how you picture your role, expectations\Nof yourself and others.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.14,1:38:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NIt would be a complicated question.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.14,1:38:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd have to look at it, you know, take five, ten minutes of asking multiple questions to\Ntry and find out what section it's coming from.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.12,1:38:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.14,1:38:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYou've tried prayer?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.14,1:38:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I have.\NI do.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.14,1:38:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NPrayer for what?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.14,1:38:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,To be an instrument.\NYeah, but that's not what you're blocked about.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.54,1:39:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're blocked about what's standing in your way.\NSo what you really ask the Holy Spirit is for a miracle of understanding about what
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.70,1:39:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you're holding in mind.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.70,1:39:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What you really want is the understanding, the awareness.\NAnd then all of a sudden you're, and then forget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.70,1:39:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're driving down the highway and all of a sudden you're like, I don't know.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.70,1:39:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to get to the house and ah, got what it is.\NCame out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.70,1:39:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.22,1:39:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of nowhere, like a flying fish.\NI don't know what happened to nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.91,1:39:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It went someplace.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.46,1:39:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot what I was going to ask.\NIf Jesus, did Jesus calibrate at a thousand throughout his entire physical lifetime?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.84,1:39:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And if so, did he, why was he attacked so viciously?\NWhy was he what?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.84,1:39:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Attacked.\NAttacked so viciously.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.84,1:39:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If he calibrated at a thousand.\NThat didn't exempt you from what you're here for.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.84,1:39:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He made a commitment, came down from heaven with no previous physical incarnation as a\Nhuman.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.51,1:40:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He served the Lord by giving up physicality.\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.54,1:40:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So he provided a service to mankind.\NHe served the truth, yes, for the sake of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.69,1:40:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,From that level, you think giving up your physical body is a great sacrifice?\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.49,1:40:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the violet flame I see when I focus on an object?\NWe can't hear you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.34,1:40:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NThe violet flame.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.34,1:40:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet flame.\NWhat is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.34,1:40:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what that refers to.\NThe Pentecostal flame you're talking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.34,1:40:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A fire, a violet fire.\NWhen I focus on things, I see a violet fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.34,1:40:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably a healing energy.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.34,1:40:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.34,1:40:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd have to research it specifically.\NI thought you knew everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.91,1:40:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dang it.\NWell, it's just like the last lady said.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.91,1:40:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, everyone has their unique little thing.\NYou have to kind of, you have to kind of, you have to kind of, you have to kind of,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.58,1:40:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to kind of, you have to kind of, you have to kind of, you have to kind of, you\Nhave to kind of, you have to kind of, you have to kind of, you have to ask several questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.11,1:41:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we're going to have to check it out, you know, individually.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.45,1:41:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NWe've only got four minutes, and four people left.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.37,1:41:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hm.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.79,1:41:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My experience of myself and a lot of other people I know is that at certain times we're\Ncapable of acting very loving and very forgiving to other people in our relationships.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.45,1:41:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.\Nother times we're still capable of having intense anger, rage, and all sorts of negative emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.31,1:41:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Does any of that have any bearing on one's overall consciousness level?\NThe fluctuating moods and emotions don't change it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.57,1:41:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What changes it is the spiritual will.\NYour calibrated level of consciousness and your karma is dependent upon the spiritual will.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.57,1:41:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So your spiritual will may be aligned in a certain way\Nand you've got some karmic whatchamacallits coming up.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.63,1:42:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the karmic propensities you have is that of humanness.\NYou've got this protoplasmic brain and its machinery.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.63,1:42:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So you transcend each of those things and handle each one as the best you can as it unwinds.\NYour life is like a CD and the story is unwinding.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.62,1:42:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?\NAnd you handle each thing as it comes up.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.88,1:42:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Do you have any questions for me?\NThat's a joke. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.15,1:42:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I was puzzled about something.\NI didn't know that my puzzlement shows so badly.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.63,1:42:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's because I would like to spend half an hour answering each question.\NAnd I'm always frustrated because there's a lot more that can be said.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.63,1:42:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be brief. I won't be half an hour.\NI didn't have a question until you started answering questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.63,1:43:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And it created one.\NYou spoke of the energy with the weird name.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.53,1:43:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI work for an agency that works with difficult to manage children.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.46,1:43:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them are the worst of the worst.\NSome of them are sexual predators.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.46,1:43:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had an experience with one of these where he was at a dark place, a low place.\NAnd there were a couple of times when I felt him drawing energy from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.06,1:43:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then as he came out of that and started to go into the abuse cycle,\Nand we were worried that he was going to, well, they call it make a bad choice, but offend.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.06,1:43:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I made a connection with him, which I took to be very negative.\NIt was very scary.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.70,1:44:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was able to feel what he felt as a predator.\NAnd I had been taught that it was like a wolf on the hunt, but it wasn't that at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.52,1:44:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a pulling from right here.\NAnd it scared me.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.68,1:44:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it really was very scary.\NAnd I felt very defiled.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.68,1:44:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like I had to be cleansed after that.\NAnd I'm wondering now if perhaps it was a backwash of that or a backwash of energy, of that energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.94,1:44:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would, I don't understand.\NThe reason Jesus Christ said to avoid evil is for that reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.51,1:44:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You make a practice of hanging out and trying to help evil.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.60,1:45:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to play with evil?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.73,1:45:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what happened.\NThat's what Jesus Christ said, avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.18,1:45:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But how do you help?\NDid Jesus Christ tell you to try and help evil?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.53,1:45:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he teach?\NHe said to avoid evil because you're not equipped to handle it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.00,1:45:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that why it scared me so?\NI wasn't expecting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.00,1:45:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're asking me a question.\NI don't want a recitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.00,1:45:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NExorcists themselves are hit by those kind of energies.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.60,1:45:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the risk you take when you work with people of that particular level.\NUnless you're extremely well guarded, extremely well guarded, it will sense a vulnerability,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.60,1:45:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,whichever chakra it might be, because you don't know your karmic inheritance from past lifetimes,\Nwhat you did to others and what you still owe.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.60,1:45:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's really playing with fire.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.30,1:45:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you got it.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.30,1:46:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.30,1:46:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You survived this far.\NPut it on your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.30,1:46:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, just one last question.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.30,1:46:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NOkay, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.30,1:46:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:09.30,1:46:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI hate to sound so tough with people.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.30,1:46:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But occasionally you have to.\NYou have to.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.30,1:46:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a hard question.\NBecause otherwise people will be in walking around in circles.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.30,1:46:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.30,1:46:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.42,1:46:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.42,1:46:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.00,1:46:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.00,1:46:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.00,1:46:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.74,1:46:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Loolooland, Lala Land.\NOkay, are we done now?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.74,1:46:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No, there's one more question.\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.14,1:46:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here's a question.\NWalking up to your walking question.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.14,1:46:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NDr. Hawkins, who are the great Masters on the planet right now,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.75,1:46:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrate between seven hundred and one thousand?\NIf you're karmically blessed or equipped,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.19,1:47:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,on to them and they yeah and you run into the experience of such a being see that comes about\Nthrough karmic inheritance and you can't name them oh you don't want to name them they get enough
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.32,1:47:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,mail as it is if you love them you know you would keep them anonymous i keep them anonymous\Ni don't have a request to hug you but if you will stand i would like to greet you in the indian way
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.45,1:47:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we acknowledge our teachers by treating their\Npersonage as sacred so if you will strand may i what should i do she wants to stand up
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.59,1:47:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,stand up oh thank you very much god bless you i realized the divinity i realized that's the\Nsacredness and the ancientness of this gesture thank you all right so i thank you all for your
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.68,1:48:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,presence i give thanks for that for i am\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.98,1:48:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,i am truly blessed by your presence amen\Noh god
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.69,1:48:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah my pen where they oh that's not a pen that's a pointer\Ni have such a collections of pointers and i keep leaving them in my baggage my luggage and
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.63,1:48:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,everywhere what good do they do me when they're home
